                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.515 Gold Bloc/73a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-04-09T15:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 9, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>72. For Ryder. As far as I can judge from a summary of the report of the Joint
                    Committee which was cabled by Deimel, the report on the whole seems to give
                    support for the trade policies which this Government has been advocating and
                    which I believe represent the direction in which action must be taken if world
                    trade is to be restored. This is to thank you for your part in preparing this
                    report.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
